<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title><![CDATA[Losing Games]]></title><description><![CDATA[Losing at D&D & other games]]></description><link>https://losing.games</link><generator>RSS for Node</generator><lastBuildDate>Wed, 28 Nov 2018 02:46:38 GMT</lastBuildDate><item><title><![CDATA[Portrait generator]]></title><link>https://losing.games/2018-11-25-portrait-generator/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://losing.games/2018-11-25-portrait-generator/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 28 Nov 2018 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;Want a portrait for the random NPC you just rolled up? This generator will create a plethora of goofy-looking characters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The generation method is fairly unsophisticated. no real attempt is made to stop the various layers from being misaligned. Most of the time it&apos;ll work, with a bit of imagination.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Play around with the the sliders for a wider range of unnatural skin colors or a more subdued palette for the clothing and hair. Use the fill style to create more print-friendly black-and-white portraits for handouts.&lt;/p&gt;
